But when the object of sovereignty is glory and good name, it leads to sincerity. Sincerity leads to piety. And sincerity inclines to all praiseworthy things. Sincerity is the opposite of falsehood. Hence it is evident that he who seeks sovereignty with this true aim leaves apermanent good name behind him.
